article.headline: Alcorn State 66, Jackson State 59
article.story: JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Trey Johnson scored 15 points to lead Alcorn State to a 66-59 victory over in-state rival Jackson State on Saturday night. Dion Callans added 12 points for Alcorn State (6-13, 5-5 Southwestern Athletic Conference). The loss dropped Jackson State (9-10, 7-3) out of a first-place tie with Mississippi Valley State in the SWAC and snapped an 11-game winning streak at home. Alcorn State ended a three-game losing streak, mainly by shooting 50 percent from the floor. The Braves did not score a free throw in the final minute but converted eight free throws to seal the win. Jackson State shot 34 percent from the floor and committed 18 turnovers. K.C. Cavette scored 19 points and Ishmael Joyce added 17 for the Tigers.
